g and equipment, and enforce strict protocols at every site.</p>            <h2>Focus on Safety</h2>          <div class="about-text">        <div class="about-grid">        <hr />        </ol>          <li><strong>5. Report and communicate:</strong> Transparent reporting to partners and continuous improvement.</li>          <li><strong>4. Track implementation:</strong> Monitoring, audits and maintenance of traceability records.</li>          <li><strong>3. Design and implement a response:</strong> Remediation plans, corrective actions, and supplier engagement.</li>          <li><strong>2. Identify and assess risks:</strong> Source data collection, supplier screening and field checks.</li>          <li><strong>1. Establish strong management systems:</strong> Policies, roles & responsibilities, and training.</li>        <ol>        <p class="cert-intro">A simple 5-step OECD-aligned due diligence framework we apply to all suppliers and shipments.</p>        <h2>Our Due Diligence Framework</h2>        <hr />        </div>            </section>                <p class="cert-note">All documents are in PDF format and require a compatible viewer. Please ensure your PDF files are placed in the `/assets/certs/` folder as instructed.</p>                </div>                    </div>                        <a href="assets/certs/icglr-rcm.pdf" class="cert-link" target="_blank">View Certificate</a>                        <p class="cert-status">Certified Exporter</p>                        <h3>ICGLR Regional Certification</h3>                    <div class="cert-card">                    <!-- Certification 4 -->          </div>            </div>              <a class="cert-link" href="assets/certs/oecd-ddg.pdf">Download (PDF)</a>              <p class="cert-status">We are aligned with the OECD Due Diligence Guidance.</p>              <h3>🛡️ OECD Aligned</h3>            <div class="product-content">
